# shadcn/ui Components

Use shadcn/ui components instead of building custom UI primitives.

## Installation

Add components via CLI:
```bash
npx shadcn@latest add button
```

## Component Usage

```tsx
// ❌ BAD - Custom button
<button className="bg-blue-500 hover:bg-blue-600 text-white px-4 py-2 rounded">
  Submit
</button>

// ✅ GOOD - shadcn/ui Button
import { Button } from "@/components/ui/button"
<Button variant="default">Submit</Button>
```

## Guidelines

- Import from `@/components/ui/*` (components live in `src/components/ui/`)
- Use built-in variants (`variant`, `size`) instead of custom styles
- Compose complex UIs from shadcn primitives (Dialog, Card, Form, etc.)
- Customize via CSS variables in `globals.css`, not inline overrides
- For forms, use shadcn Form components with react-hook-form + zod

## Common Components

| Need | Component |
|------|-----------|
| Buttons | `Button` |
| Forms | `Form`, `Input`, `Select`, `Checkbox` |
| Feedback | `Toast`, `Alert`, `Dialog` |
| Layout | `Card`, `Separator`, `Tabs` |
| Data | `Table`, `DataTable` |
